data.title: Toni Morrison, author of The Bluest Eye and Beloved, among other novels, was the first Black woman to win a Nobel Prize. She was awarded by...
data.meta_description:
14 likes, 0 comments - youthcastmgrp on April 6, 2024: "Toni Morrison, author of The Bluest Eye and Beloved, among other novels, was the first Black woman to win a Nobel Prize. She was awarded by President Barack Obama for her unapologetic passion and deep connection to the black community, sharing the ups and downs of life. YMG Intern Aabri Spear shares more about her achievements. 

#womenshistorymonth #nobelprize #poetry #literature #reading #tonimorrison #blackauthor #author #writing #readmore".
